caption: I went there for the first time for lunch and they have a huge selection of sandwiches. I had a meatball sub and it was the best I ever had.
Wraps rock
I had the salmon and rice...delicious
I love this place!! They are the best!! I have been enjoying their subs since they first open down by CUNY college. Variety of everything.The chicken noodle soup is awesome!!
Best for sammiches. They are so good.  I'm eating a modified CC Blue without the blue and with pepper jack, bacon, and pickles today.  It's heaven.
Deli's are perfect for breakfast, fresh&tasty. Pricing is fine.
Good sandwiches, fast and friendly service.
Best bagels in NY

The wife of the owner of this business is extremely mean. I pity the people who work here especially the delivery guys. This woman  basically has the owner ( her husband  in her back pocket) that said..  Its a go to place for students in the neighbourhood. Just a regular spot. Thrives best for quick breakfast bites in harlem. Not excited to recommend. Their so called muffins and cakes spend weeks in the self. Sorry to say.. coffee machine dead on arrival. My opinion though... yours may differ. Good luck!
I adore Subconscious! They are so warm. I can’t believe how fast they are able to work.

They are known for their subs and their subs are SUBPAR and tasteless.  The "free" chicken noodle soup was disgusting as the chicken in the soup had blue color dots. I threw away the soup immediately.

I've been here a few times. Their subs are okay, but they're really not a stand out from the average deli, which is a little disappointing from a place that claims to specialize in them. If you're a Columbia student, remember to ask for the discount.

Lots of choices for sandwiches and salads made to order. I had the Twice as Nice which was tasty. Got chips and soda to go with it. A little pricey. Pretty quickly made if you’re in a time crunch. Staff was pleasant.
The wait is a little long, and the space is a little crowded, but the subs are some of the best in NY, and the free soup is a nice touch.
An awesome place for budget salads
Absolutely awesome. Nuclear wrap & Lifeguard are out of this world so far. Will be going again shortly.
Those are some delicious subs. Perfect for hangovers or just a greasy lunch craving.
Just an overpriced bodega that services Columbia kids, get a slice next door
Good choice of subs and salads. Affordable prices, and they offer 10% discount for students and professors of Columbia. Ask if a soup comes free with salad.
The food maker cut a decent amount of raw beef, then used the same knife to cut my wrap! Will not come back anymore, disgusting...
I ordered the chicken fajita panini. Compared to 5 years ago, I feel the taste has dropped. Panini was not hot enough. Do remember to ask for the panini to be grilled longer if you prefer it hotter.
An affordable option for salad, sandwiches, sweets, etc... The salad I got here was amazing and I will definitely return in the future.
Made to order sandwiches with the occasional $1 iced coffee: delish.
The sandwich here is superb! I recommend final exam. It's huge and I can eat for two meals.And the price is fair. The salad is great. Avacado and strawberry are so fresh

I don't understand why this place doesn't have better reviews. Maybe it's because people just haven't tried the right sandwiches? With that said, when I tried a couple of the vegetarian options, I thought it was very good. But once I tried their meat options, particularly the GPA and Final Exam, that's when I was sold on how great this place is.  The Final Exam is probably one of the best sandwiches I've ever had, and if you eat all the meats in this sandwich, this is definitely what you should order. Otherwise, the GPA is also a great option.  UPDATE: the quality of this place has gone down significantly over the last couple of years. :(

Tiny place that leaves a big impression! Taste and service makes me want to return. Never had a disappointing sandwich because they are consistently good tasting. Give them a try anytime you are in the area!

Terrible service by one of the cooks! We've always ordered from here through seamless or come in person and had great experiences. However, since you cannot longer order breakfast online, I came in person.  The server who assisted me was clearly having a bad day and took it out on me. All I wanted was a breakfast sandwich and he kept acting annoyed and asking me the same questions over and over. Wish I would have gone to Joe's instead.  While our department enjoys their food, I will have to think twice about coming here again.
Great! I recommend the delicious IQ sandwich.

Very bad experience. I'm a vegetarian and took the vegan wrap and they mistakenly put a chicken piece in it, which I found while eating. I asked them to refund me money and they said that they can give me another one. I said no and yet they gave me another one. Money and food both wasted. They also had poor chocolate cake that tasted stale.
Great food!!love it
Great service and food. Def going back for lunch.
This is a cute little sandwich place. Their hours aren't great, and they are closed on Sundays. We've enjoyed their sandwich + beer special on occasion. Wish they had more/better outdoor seating.
Huge portion of food. Fun name of sandwiches.
food is expensive and not good - so uh avoid
One of the few places where you can get hot sandwiches!

I ordered Yesterday Through Seamless and the Sandwiches Were Made at 1230pm, i Got my Sandwiches Delivered at 215pm When They Finally Arrived Both Sandwiches and Fries Were Soggy The Bread was Just A Disaster it Wouldnt even Hold the Contents. I called Seamless and they tried to contact the Business to get a Refund but there hasnt been a Manager in Till Today No Response They just offered me a free Sandwich, i Denied i Dont want Any Sandwiches From This Unreliable and Unprossional Business Ever Again
Good food great service friendly staff!

They made my burger just the way I asked them to and were very pleasant about it. They even joked with me a little when I paid, so I walked out feeling good about the whole experience. Nothing too special about what I ate, but it was good. The chicken noodle soup that came with my burger and fries (a bonus I was not expecting) was yummy too.
This the best place to get a sandwich 🥪

Out of the five times I went there, three times they bumped the price up one or two dollars. I like the food and the price, but not when they charge you more than expected. The woman cashier is terrible. She doesn’t even know the price and tried to bump up two dollars and got angry at me instead. Also she charged two dollars for a 1.25 dollar coffee. The one dollar discount if you show the columbia ID card doesn’t work as well. One time they charged me one extra dollars for showing the ID card. It’s not a big deal so I didn’t say much, but it just not great when this KEEPS happening. They should definitely learn more math before opening the store.
Awesome sandwich!!!
Limited Vegan options. Super greasy. Not value for money. They did not have the soup they advertised for. Disappointed
One of the best places for awesome variety of sandwiches and free soup ;-)
Open hours are a lie. It’s 7 pm on a Saturday. Not open.
Great sandwiches and clean place
The bread I bought was over date and got mildew on it, highly not recommended.

Quick and good lunch place for anyone in the Columbia University area. Columbia students and employees also receive a discount. You get a free soup with a salad or sandwich purchase. The soup changes every day.

Overall, really good location (close to Columbia and CSSW). Prices are really great! $2.18 for a large iced coffee- and while it wasnt the best i've ever had it was definitely worth the money. Their bagels, sandwiches and food are very reasonably priced!
Greasy food.
Food is excellent, staff is nice.
Delicious and massive subs. Didn't love the cookies.
Surprised this place doesn't have a higher rating. Great food and very good price. 10% off for Columbia students
Great food lots of variety and reasonably priced. Sad that they haven't reopened their 140th location
I got the “final exam”. Lunch time is best because it comes with soup. The price is decent and service is good enough for deli. The fish is a bit salty.
Quick service but over priced.
Not a bad place to take out some sandwitches. Decent menu selections.
Vegan wrap with provolone and falafel. Plus a Brooklyn crafted ginger beer and fires with chipotle 14.99 Can't beat the service.

Got a vegan wrap. I liked it but it was very small for the price. I had to wait a little longer than you would want in a quick bite spot. Oh, your clothes will smell oily the whole day after you wait there for 5 minutes for your sandwich.

When I do not know what to eat, I probably will eat a sandwich, and Subsconscious has helped me with that dilemma on a few occasions. Their sandwiches are also quite good when they are not coming to rescue me from being brain-dead with hunger or tired or whatever.
Friendly place good food fair price in this area
Even in very busy times, you can get quick and cheerful service. Sandwiches and soup here are delicious!
Great place for sandwiches. I recommend to try the final exam sub!
I love the sandwiches here.  They are fast, delicious and affordable.
Dinner specials where each sub comes with soup makes for a great deal. Final Exam & GPA are both delicious. Get some onion rings.
Large selection, but the sandwich was pretty bland.
Huge selection of hot and cold sandwiches. They also serve breakfast options. Not a lot of seating inside, so large groups will want it to-go.
Simple American food. Quick to eat and healthy
Their hot sandwiches are pretty stuffed for how much you pay.

This used to be a good place. Good sandwiches, not pricey. After a reform (owner changed?), they recruited so many new staff, who are not good at making sandwiches. This lowered the quality of the food. They also raised the prices.
Good, not great subs. Nice soup special, normal prices for NYC. If you're looking to eat for under $10 and walking by you should stop by, although it's not the best place around
My first time going the food was great. They do not have seating which the reason for 4 and not five stars.
Spinach salad with chicken, cheese bacon and 1egg cost me $14... no wonder this franchise is being fazed out. This use to be my spot...NOT ANY MORE .
Decent (if somewhat overpriced) sandwiches served at the end of a long line/ wait. If you are pressed for time, consider calling your order ahead.

Pretty okay place for a sub. They'll make it however you want, and there's a great set of options. Vegetarians are out of luck here -- you'll end up with a pretty sad sandwich. But hey, you made that decision. Better than Subway, that's for sure.

The cooks will treat you with respect if you approach them with a smile (as you should), but if you're on your phone, or are rude, expect similar service. The food is above average, the cashiers are very friendly, but it can get busy (expect at least a 5 minute wait during the breakfast/lunch rush).

Cool deli near Columbia University. Expect to find any and everything from sandwiches to bagels and unique spreads. Great place to go for a quick stop before running to class. The prices are also very reasonable. Although, the vegetable cream cheese I had on my bagel one time didn't taste too well.

The service here leaves something less than desired here. Apparently the prices aren't the board aren't the right prices. Sandwiches seem to have gone up a dollar from what is posted. I didn't see the sign about price increase anywhere. The sandwiches are good but definitely not worth almost $10

This place is definitely one of the worst places to eat near Columbia. Not only is the food quality incredibly poor, but the service is also just as awful. Don't ever think of asking them to cater since they will show up late and bring only half the food you ordered while charging you the full price. In conclusion, just an awful experience all around.
Their burgers are superb!
Great vegetarian sub. Had many grilled veggies.
Ordinarily sandwiches, pretty quick turn around. If you are right there, try it once. Not a place to walk for though with other sandwich places(CrackDel anyone) pretty close by.

This sub shop is fairly convienent to columbia and has good food. The structure to order is somewhat confusing and the shop is fairly cramped. The food is on the pricier side but the options are many. often has a long wait from order to payment.

great, convenient. There was a time that the day would not be complete without going here for some $1.50 coffee or a sandwich. The sub is the best deal; for $1 more, you get double the food. You can't sit down here, though.
It's a little crowded and sometimes they aren't that friendly, but the food is good and prices are reasonable.  Bagels are great!
